exportRelationNodes

private <T extends INode<T>> int exportRelationNodes(java.io.Writer writer,
                                                     IGraph<T> graph,
                                                     java.lang.String relation,
                                                     java.util.LinkedList<WeightedTransition<T>> allTransitions,
                                                     java.util.LinkedHashMap<T,java.lang.Integer> nodeToInt,
                                                     int nodeCnt)
                         throws java.io.IOException
Exports all the nodes in the graph for a particular relation, using output stream writer. This function only exports the nodes, but it also builds up a list of allTransitions that these nodes include, maintains a nodeCnt (which is then returned), and also maintains the nodeToInt map. All of these are also passed as arguments.

Type Parameters:
T - The node type in the graph being exported
Parameters:
writer - The writer to use for writing out node records
graph - The graph whose nodes will be exported
relation - The relation to export (must be present in graph)
allTransitions - A list of transitions that will be modified to include transitions in graph.
nodeToInt - A mapping between nodes in the graph and the node's id in the dot output file. This is used to consistently output transitions between nodes.
nodeCnt - The node count -- used to generate unique node ids in nodeToInt map
Returns:
the updated node count
Throws:
java.io.IOException - in case there is a problem using the writer

exportGraphCanonically

private <T extends INode<T>> void exportGraphCanonically(java.io.Writer writer,
                                                         IGraph<T> graph,
                                                         boolean isInitialGraph)
                             throws java.io.IOException
Exports a graph in a dot format using the writer. It does so canonically -- two isomorphic graphs will have equivalent dot outputs. The generated Graphviz dot files may then be diff-ed to check if they represent the same graphs.

Type Parameters:
T - Graph node type
Parameters:
writer - The writer to use for dot output
graph - The graph to export
Throws:
java.io.IOException - In case there is a problem using the writer
